<Content>Noisiest hotel ever I travel often to Barcelona and the office booked me this hotel to me close to the meeting room.Arrived at the hotel around 2pm, check out was easy.Got a room on the 3RD floor,Rooms are noisy as they have no double glazing and the hotel is downtown. Then the cleaners are making horrendous noise, i can't even talk by phone.Ask the reception to do something and they say, they can't !!!It's quite expensive and definetely do not recommend this place for persons who want to sleep in the morning or work from their room.Awful noise, awful staff, and not even a nice location. 
